#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:2
msgid "_ - call fish's translations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:5
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:7
msgid "_ STRING"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:12
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:14
msgid "``_`` translates its arguments into the current language, if possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:16
msgid ""
"This only works with messages which are translated as part of fish's own "
"sources, so using it as part of your own fish scripts which are not "
"upstreamed into the fish repo will not work unless the exact same message "
"also exists upstream."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:18
msgid ""
"It requires fish to be built with gettext support. If that support is "
"disabled or there is no translation it will echo the argument back."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:20
msgid ""
"The language depends on the current locale, set with :envvar:`LANG`, :envvar:"
"`LC_MESSAGES`, :envvar:`LC_ALL`, and :envvar:`LANGUAGE`. These variables do "
"not have to be exported for fish to use them, and fish's variable scopes are "
"supported. If other programs launched via fish should respect these locale "
"variables they have to be exported to make them available outside of fish."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:24
msgid ""
"For :envvar:`LANGUAGE` you can use a list, or use colons to separate "
"multiple languages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:26
msgid ""
"If the :ref:`status language set <status-language>` command was used, its "
"arguments specify the language precedence, and the environment variables are "
"ignored."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:29
msgid "Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:31
msgid "``_`` takes no options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:34
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:36
msgid "Use German translations::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:38
msgid ""
"> set LANG de_DE.UTF-8\n"
"> _ file\n"
"Datei"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:42
msgid ""
"Specify a precedence of languages (only works with :envvar:`LANGUAGE`)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:44
msgid ""
"> set LANGUAGE pt de\n"
"> _ file  # This message has a Portuguese translation.\n"
"arquivo\n"
"> _ \"Invalid arguments\"  # This message does not have a Portuguese "
"translation, but a German one.\n"
"Ungültige Argumente\n"
"> _ untranslatable  # No translation in Portuguese, nor in German.\n"
"untranslatable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/_.rst:52
msgid ""
"Note that the specific examples may change if translations are added/"
"modified."
msgstr ""
